# Git Flow branch names (PR source branches)

Enforced by `.github/workflows/branch-protection.yml`. Human-readable rules: **CONTRIBUTING.md** §2 Branching (Branch Protection).

## PRs targeting `develop`

The **head** branch name must match one of:

- `feature/*`
- `fix/*`
- `chore/*` (use for **CI/CD**, GitHub Actions, and tooling—there is **no** `ci/*` prefix)
- `dependabot/*`
- `release/*`
- `hotfix/*`
- exactly `main` (back-merge after release/hotfix)

**Not allowed** for PRs to `develop`: `ci/*`, `refactor/*`, or other prefixes. Rename to `chore/…` (or `fix/…` / `feature/…` as appropriate).

## PRs targeting `main`

The **head** branch must be `release/*` or `hotfix/*` only.

## PR descriptions

Draft file path `.pr-descriptions/<branch-name>.md` uses the **actual** branch name (may contain `/`); see **pr-description-workflow.mdc**.
